{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We assume each worker exclusively occupies one GPU to run the DNN to serve inference requests.",
    "More fine-grained GPU sharing mechanisms such as NVIDIA multi-process service (MPS) or multi-instance GPU (MIG) can also be employed (Yu et al. 2022), where each instance is treated as a separate worker.",
    "The DNN execution time is highly predictable (Gujarati et al. 2020), so we use DNN latency profiles obtained offline for online latency prediction.",
    "Suppose the system is serving a set of clients given by ℂ = {c 1, c 2,..., c N }.",
    "Each of the clients c i generates inference requests with input size s i at rate i."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "More fine-grained GPU sharing mechanisms such as NVIDIA multi-process service (MPS) or multi-instance GPU (MIG) can also be employed (Yu et al. 2022), where each instance is treated as a separate worker.",
    "The DNN execution time is highly predictable (Gujarati et al. 2020), so we use DNN latency profiles obtained offline for online latency prediction."
